<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=HVAC&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> <i>Designer's Guide to Ceiling-Based Air Diffusion</i>, Rock and Zhu, <a href="/wiki/ASHRAE" title="ASHRAE" class="mw-redirect">ASHRAE</a>, Inc., Atlanta, GA, USA, 2002</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/279869/hypocaust" class="external text" title="http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/279869/hypocaust" rel="nofollow">"Hypocaust"</a>. <i>Encyclopedic</i>. Britannica Online. 2009<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/279869/hypocaust" class="external free" title="http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/279869/hypocaust" rel="nofollow">http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/279869/hypocaust</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2009-01-29</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Hypocaust&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopedic&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.pub=Britannica+Online&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2FEBchecked%2Ftopic%2F279869%2Fhypocaust&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:HVAC"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
